The police used tear gas and live rounds to disperse large demonstrations in Kinshasa staged by activists upset that presidential elections have been delayed into next year. News services reported numerous injuries and dozens of arrests. President Joseph Kabila, the transitional leader, will remain in office until the nationwide elections are held. A peace deal that ended years of war in Congo set June 30 as the election day but allowed the government to delay voting for up to a year. Marc Lacey (NYT)